WEBVTT

00:01.357 --> 00:03.324
You took this case
without running it by me.

00:03.360 --> 00:04.826
- Jessica--
- That's enough. Dump it.

00:04.861 --> 00:06.094
Or I will.

00:06.129 --> 00:07.028
You think
this case is a winner?

00:07.063 --> 00:08.063
I do.

00:08.064 --> 00:09.597
Then what do you say
we do it together?

00:09.632 --> 00:11.032
(Rachel) I'm afraid you're gonna end up
hating each other.

00:11.067 --> 00:13.267
If I'm lucky, I'm gonna fight
with him about a lot of things.

00:13.303 --> 00:15.753
Why not start with a fight where
we're both on the same side?

00:15.805 --> 00:17.538
This is Harvey's
last three income statements,

00:17.574 --> 00:19.223
and I found them
sitting in the copy machine.

00:19.259 --> 00:20.775
You came to work for me.

00:20.810 --> 00:22.050
You knew who I was
when you did,

00:22.078 --> 00:23.277
so now it's time
for you to decide.

00:23.313 --> 00:24.412
Are you with me or not?

00:24.447 --> 00:26.280
You always said,
once you pick a side,

00:26.316 --> 00:27.315
if you're not loyal
to that side,

00:27.350 --> 00:28.716
then who the hell are you?

00:28.752 --> 00:30.251
You should've thought of that
before you picked someone

00:30.253 --> 00:32.293
who would do something like this
in the first place.

00:33.239 --> 00:36.090
You ever take sides with
Jack Soloff against me again,

00:36.126 --> 00:38.126
I will bury you.

00:42.799 --> 00:45.166
[elevator bell dings]
- Well, you look happy.

00:45.201 --> 00:47.151
Becky just tell Susie
she like-likes you?

00:47.203 --> 00:49.504
Eh, more like Kelton Insurance
just told Robert Zane

00:49.539 --> 00:51.005
they're scared-scared of us.

00:51.041 --> 00:52.006
You got a settlement offer?

00:52.042 --> 00:53.408
Just like he said
we would.

00:53.443 --> 00:55.593
I got to hand it to him,
he played them perfectly.

00:55.645 --> 00:57.311
Did he now?

00:57.364 --> 00:58.379
What?

00:58.415 --> 00:59.415
Nothing.

00:59.416 --> 01:01.015
Look, I take it back
about Becky.

01:01.051 --> 01:02.750
The only one with a crush
around here is you.

01:02.802 --> 01:04.385
Sounds like someone's worried
that Robert Zane

01:04.437 --> 01:05.720
might be better than him.

01:05.772 --> 01:08.689
Nice try, tiger, but did Magic
ever worry about Bird?

01:08.691 --> 01:09.690
First of all, yes, he did.

01:09.692 --> 01:10.792
Second of all, you realize

01:10.827 --> 01:12.043
you're the white guy
in this scenario, right?

01:12.078 --> 01:13.811
I know I'm the bigger badass
in every scenario.

01:13.847 --> 01:17.081
Okay, Mr. Badass, which one
are you, Magic or Bird?

01:17.133 --> 01:18.266
I think we both know
I'm...

01:18.301 --> 01:20.118
(both)
Jordan.

01:20.170 --> 01:22.653
Hey, why don't you go meet
your boyfriend Robert Zane?

01:22.689 --> 01:24.705
I think I just left something
at security.

01:24.741 --> 01:28.376
Oh. Look who like-likes
someone now.

01:28.411 --> 01:30.111
Ma'am, the last time
I let someone up

01:30.146 --> 01:31.712
that he wasn't expecting,

01:31.748 --> 01:33.481
he threatened
to have me executed.

01:33.516 --> 01:36.117
I'm sure he did,
but I'm telling you that--

01:36.152 --> 01:38.453
That Gretchen obviously forgot
to phone down, Carl,

01:38.488 --> 01:41.122
because we have a meeting
scheduled for right now.

01:41.157 --> 01:42.323
That isn't what she just--

01:42.358 --> 01:44.859
Carl.

01:48.765 --> 01:51.365
A meeting with you.
Really?

01:51.418 --> 01:53.134
I promise
I'm much better-looking

01:53.169 --> 01:54.569
than whoever
you were supposed to meet.

01:54.604 --> 01:57.738
You have no idea
how right you are.

01:57.774 --> 01:59.874
But I could have sworn
you were just on your way out.

01:59.909 --> 02:02.176
Oh, that's not a problem.
The mayor can wait.

02:02.212 --> 02:04.846
But I'm not sure
the governor can.

02:04.881 --> 02:06.614
Are you trying
to out-name-drop me?

02:06.649 --> 02:09.150
If I were,
I think I just did.

02:09.185 --> 02:12.587
But I'll let you in
on a little secret.

02:12.622 --> 02:14.956
I don't really care
about names that much.

02:14.991 --> 02:16.390
Well, if you don't care
about names, why don't we

02:16.426 --> 02:18.726
skip the introductions
and just get down to breakfast?

02:18.761 --> 02:20.211
What if I already
had breakfast?

02:20.246 --> 02:22.897
I'm talking about
tomorrow morning, in my kitchen.

02:22.932 --> 02:25.566
Or yours, I mean, you look like
you have a nice place.

02:28.888 --> 02:34.041
As tempting as that is,
maybe another time.

02:36.846 --> 02:38.079
Good luck
in your meeting.

02:42.051 --> 02:44.952
So how's my favorite
pain-in-the-ass lawyer?

02:44.988 --> 02:47.488
I thought Louis was your
favorite pain-in-the-ass lawyer.

02:47.524 --> 02:50.658
He is, but Louis
isn't responsible

02:50.710 --> 02:52.627
for me getting to work
on this.

02:55.999 --> 02:58.332
You're doing the grunt work
on our case?

02:58.368 --> 02:59.967
I pulled some strings--
thought it might give us

03:00.003 --> 03:01.102
a chance
to work together.

03:01.137 --> 03:03.237
You know I'm engaged,
right?

03:03.273 --> 03:04.639
Yes, Mike,
that's my plan,

03:04.674 --> 03:06.374
to steal you
from my boss's daughter.

03:06.409 --> 03:09.377
It's a thing.
It's been done.

03:09.412 --> 03:11.362
Well, I didn't come here
to steal you.

03:11.397 --> 03:13.981
I came here
to thank you.

03:14.017 --> 03:14.949
For what?

03:14.984 --> 03:15.883
Come on, Mike.

03:15.919 --> 03:17.185
I get fired,

03:17.220 --> 03:20.154
and two days later, I get
an offer from Rachel's father?

03:20.190 --> 03:23.424
Whatever you did,
I owe you one.

03:23.459 --> 03:25.359
Actually,
you owe Rachel one.

03:25.395 --> 03:27.128
No shit.

03:27.163 --> 03:29.597
Shit.

03:29.632 --> 03:32.517
(both as Clay Davis from <i> The Wire)</i>
Shiiit.

03:34.404 --> 03:37.438
By the way, you're
in the wrong conference room.

03:43.079 --> 03:44.712
Okay, Esther,
what are you doing here?

03:44.747 --> 03:46.814
What,
a woman can't stop by

03:46.816 --> 03:48.349
to see her brother,
who she loves?

03:48.384 --> 03:51.485
Please, you know damn well
we don't love each other.

03:51.521 --> 03:54.755
In that case,
I need a lawyer.

03:54.791 --> 03:56.424
[laughs]
You? For what?

03:56.459 --> 03:59.594
Did you give someone salmonella
with your stupid muffins?

03:59.629 --> 04:00.962
I'm getting a divorce.

04:04.417 --> 04:06.167
Well, good.

04:06.202 --> 04:07.935
I knew that guy was dead weight
the second I met him.

04:07.971 --> 04:10.538
I know, I think that was
your speech at our wedding.

04:10.540 --> 04:12.373
And your sympathy
is touching,

04:12.408 --> 04:14.659
but I didn't come here
to vindicate you.

04:14.694 --> 04:15.743
No, I know you didn't.

04:15.745 --> 04:17.043
You came to get me

04:17.079 --> 04:19.346
to slaughter Jeffrey for you,
and I will.

04:19.382 --> 04:21.616
When I'm done with him,
he won't have a pot to shit in.

04:21.618 --> 04:23.751
It's "piss in."

04:23.786 --> 04:25.820
And, Louis, I don't want you
to slaughter Jeffrey.

04:25.855 --> 04:26.787
Why the hell not?

04:26.823 --> 04:28.356
Because I want
Harvey Specter to.

04:28.391 --> 04:29.423
Come again?

04:29.459 --> 04:31.025
You said he was
the best attorney in the city.

04:31.060 --> 04:32.927
No, Esther, I told you
he was my best friend.

04:32.962 --> 04:35.296
Which is exactly what you said
about Jeremy Henschell

04:35.331 --> 04:37.081
in tenth grade,
which really meant

04:37.133 --> 04:38.866
you worshipped him
from afar,

04:38.901 --> 04:40.368
you wrote in your diary
about him,

04:40.403 --> 04:42.436
and you never
actually hung out.

04:42.472 --> 04:44.105
Okay, you swore
you never read my diary.

04:44.157 --> 04:46.274
And you swore you didn't spy
on me and Jeremy.

04:46.276 --> 04:47.441
Oh, please,
that was one time.

04:47.493 --> 04:48.943
I was on my way
to get a glass of milk,

04:48.995 --> 04:50.111
and for your information,

04:50.113 --> 04:51.445
I've been lactose intolerant
ever since.

04:51.447 --> 04:52.913
Louis, are you gonna
get me Harvey,

04:52.949 --> 04:54.498
or do I have to get him
myself?

04:54.534 --> 04:57.752
Harvey is not taking on
any new clients right now,

04:57.787 --> 05:00.788
and he's out of town
for the next few years.

05:02.675 --> 05:05.626
Louis, I know
what you're doing.

05:05.678 --> 05:07.628
You think I want Harvey
because I don't think

05:07.630 --> 05:09.213
you're good enough.

05:09.265 --> 05:11.182
You're wrong.

05:11.217 --> 05:13.301
I know how good you are,

05:13.353 --> 05:14.685
but this is personal for me,

05:14.721 --> 05:16.771
which means
it will be personal for you,

05:16.806 --> 05:20.524
and I can't have that.

05:20.560 --> 05:23.811
So please,
will you get me Harvey?

05:25.315 --> 05:28.316
I'll make it happen.

05:29.736 --> 05:32.486
Thank you, Louis.

05:38.628 --> 05:40.161
That was Esther?

05:40.163 --> 05:41.912
Yes, I know what you're gonna
say--we look exactly alike.

05:41.964 --> 05:43.047
That actually wasn't--

05:43.082 --> 05:44.215
I get it--it's like
looking at me in a wig.

05:44.250 --> 05:45.299
I've heard it
a thousand times.

05:45.335 --> 05:48.753
Yeah, the resemblance
is uncanny.

05:48.805 --> 05:50.338
What?

05:50.340 --> 05:51.972
I'm just wondering why you're
not getting up to go ask Harvey.

05:52.008 --> 05:53.174
Because I'm not gonna
ask him.

05:53.176 --> 05:55.226
I'm gonna save some time
and tell her he said no.

05:55.261 --> 05:56.394
Louis--

05:56.429 --> 05:58.562
Donna, we all know
that Harvey's furious at me.

05:58.598 --> 05:59.730
There's no way
he's gonna do it.

05:59.766 --> 06:02.316
Maybe not.

06:02.352 --> 06:04.935
But, Louis, she's family,

06:04.987 --> 06:07.988
and if there's one thing that
Harvey understands, it's that.

06:10.860 --> 06:12.109
Where the hell have you been?

06:12.161 --> 06:14.362
Sorry, I got stuck
in really bad traffic.

06:14.414 --> 06:16.747
So you were
in the wrong conference room.

06:16.783 --> 06:19.200
For about 20 minutes.

06:19.202 --> 06:21.786
So what did we get?

06:21.838 --> 06:23.754
Want to take a guess?

06:23.790 --> 06:24.922
$90 million.

06:24.957 --> 06:27.007
Want to take a real guess?

06:27.043 --> 06:28.043
That was a real guess.

06:28.044 --> 06:29.477
Son, what planet
are you living on?

06:29.512 --> 06:30.478
The planet
where you called

06:30.513 --> 06:32.046
to say we got
a great settlement.

06:32.081 --> 06:35.316
$25 million is
a great settlement.

06:35.351 --> 06:36.283
$25 million?

06:36.319 --> 06:38.052
Robert, after fees,

06:38.087 --> 06:40.121
that's less than $70,000
per person.

06:40.156 --> 06:41.956
[laughs] Then what do you
suggest we counter with?

06:41.991 --> 06:43.691
I suggest we counter
with a trial.

06:43.726 --> 06:45.142
Are you nuts?
You don't go to trial.

06:45.178 --> 06:47.061
You turn up the pressure,
and then you settle.

06:47.063 --> 06:49.163
Going to trial is
turning up the pressure.

06:49.198 --> 06:50.848
The second we finish
opening arguments,

06:50.883 --> 06:52.199
that offer is
gonna triple.

06:52.235 --> 06:54.201
Look, I've sat across the table
from these two

06:54.203 --> 06:55.419
four times
in the last six years,

06:55.471 --> 06:56.754
and when they say
this is their best offer,

06:56.806 --> 06:58.739
it's their best offer,
and we're recommending it.

06:58.775 --> 07:00.074
Well, you can recommend
whatever you want.

07:00.109 --> 07:01.208
I'm recommending
we reject it.

07:01.210 --> 07:04.211
You don't give clients
conflicting opinions.

07:04.247 --> 07:05.647
You work it out
behind closed doors.

07:05.648 --> 07:06.697
Well, maybe that's the problem.

07:06.749 --> 07:08.332
You want to do things
behind closed doors.

07:08.367 --> 07:09.383
I actually want to be honest.

07:09.419 --> 07:10.384
Hey, watch yourself, Mike.

07:10.436 --> 07:13.020
You tell me this,
would $70,000 per person

07:13.022 --> 07:14.755
be a great settlement
if we were talking

07:14.791 --> 07:16.173
about Laura's life
or Rachel's?

07:16.225 --> 07:17.625
You get out of here!

07:17.660 --> 07:18.859
You don't come back

07:18.911 --> 07:20.694
until you wrap your head
around recommending this offer.

07:20.747 --> 07:23.030
And don't you ever
use them against me again!

